      "writtenOn": "2018-07-16T01:28:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e this is /very/ slight... the cost of len(Files) move calls, right?\n\nYes, it is O(len(files)) number of FS metadata calls (moves, stats, mkdirs). It does add up for packages with lots of small files (like e.g. GAE sdk package), even on fast machines.\n\nBUT, for repairs, I don\u0027t care. Repairs shouldn\u0027t be a regular event.\n\n\u003e Couldn\u0027t we further make this generically faster by parallelizing the move operations (so we spend less time in userspace between syscalls?)...\n\nProbably. IIRC, I tried some time ago, it gives no noticeable improvement, at least on OSX (probably hitting some lock in the kernel).\n\n\u003e assuming it\u0027s worth speeding up at all? (SD card RPi\u0027s?). Maybe only if len(Files) \u003e 500 or something?\n\nNeeds experimentation.",
      "parentUuid": "1947649c_2f67f1be",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 531,
        "startChar": 21,
        "endLine": 531,
        "endChar": 29
      },
      "revId": "ad599d3e073b8ac2b70dec3e7867dc88655535c6",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
