      "writtenOn": "2018-07-16T01:28:17Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Hm... is there a way we could accumulate this error and only show it at the end (so that the tool still exits !0, but we repair as much as we can?). \n\nOk, returning an error now.\n\n\u003e Could/should we abort and redeploy the entire thing if this happens?\n\nThis is a more complicated change, since we may not have PackageInstance here, and need to ask cipd.Client to fetch it first. This is further complicated by the retry loop in cipd.Client for handling of broken cached files.\n\nI\u0027m 80% sure we\u0027ll never see this repair errors (or rather, the errors we\u0027ll see will be related to file system permissions, or bad disks, and thus won\u0027t be fixable by full reinstall either). So I prefer to punt on this for now and improve only if needed.",
